dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
dcterms:description: CIFAR10 is a dataset containing 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR10

dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
dcterms:description: CIFAR100 is a dataset containing 60,000 32x32 color images in 100 classes, with 600 images per class. It is used for more fine-grained image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR100

dcterms:description: Webvision is a large-scale dataset containing 2.4 million images crawled from the web, covering 1,000 classes from the ImageNet dataset. It is used for training models in the presence of noisy labels.

dcterms:description: Clothing1M is a large dataset consisting of 1 million images of clothing articles, collected from e-commerce websites. It contains noisy labels and is used for image classification tasks.
